[SECTION: Market & Business Model]
5. Market Opportunity — TAM/SAM/SOM 3-year bottom-up build (include bar chart: TAM SAM SOM $B)
6. Business Model — revenue streams, unit economics, LTV to CAC ratio (include bar chart: ARR by revenue stream $M)
7. Traction & Key Metrics — MoM growth, retention, NRR, logo count (include line chart: ARR growth over 12 months $M)
8. Competitive Landscape — named competitors, differentiation matrix, why we win
[SECTION: Plan & Ask]
9. Go-to-Market — channel mix, CAC, sales cycle, expansion motion
10. Financial Projections — 3-year model: ARR, gross margin, burn, path to profitability (include bar chart: ARR and gross profit $M by year)
11. Team & Advisors — founder bios, relevant experience, board members
12. The Ask — raise amount, use of funds breakdown (include doughnut chart: use of funds % breakdown)'
};
const dtLabel = { gtm: 'Go-to-Market', strategy: 'Corporate Strategy', diagnostic: 'Operational Diagnostic', investor: 'Investor Pitch' };
const frameworkNote = {
  gtm: 'Apply Porter Five Forces for market attractiveness, TAM/SAM/SOM bottom-up build, and AARRR funnel for channel analysis.',
  strategy: 'Apply MECE issue trees, SCR narrative structure (Situation-Complication-Resolution), and BCG matrix for portfolio prioritization.',
  diagnostic: 'Apply EBITDA bridge analysis, root cause fishbone diagram, and maturity model scoring on a 1-5 scale for capability assessment.',
  investor: 'Follow VC-standard Sequoia deck format: problem then solution then market then traction then team then ask. All metrics must be real or clearly labelled as projections.'
};
const slideStructure = 'REQUIRED SLIDE STRUCTURE FOR ' + (dtLabel[deck_type] || deck_type).toUpperCase() + ' DECK:
' + (STRUCTURES[deck_type] || STRUCTURES.gtm);
const data = ['ENGAGEMENT DATA:', 'Client: ' + client_name, 'Industry: ' + industry, 'Deck Type: ' + (dtLabel[deck_type] || deck_type), 'Project Title: ' + deck_title, 'Client Brief: ' + requirements, 'Market Research: ' + research, 'Quality Review Feedback (incorporate all suggestions): ' + quality].join('
');
const jsonFmt = ['OUTPUT FORMAT: Return ONLY valid JSON. No markdown fences. No preamble. No commentary after the JSON.', '{"slides": [', '  { "type": "title", "title": "<Deck Title>", "subtitle": "<Month YYYY | ' + client_name + ' | Strictly Confidential>" },', '  { "type": "section_header", "title": "<Section Topic>", "subtitle": "<One sentence framing the section>" },', '  { "type": "content", "title": "<Action headline: verb + specific number + business outcome>", "subtitle": "<One sharp So What insight>",', '    "bullets": [{ "text": "<assertion 15-25 words with %, $, or timeframe>", "sub_points": ["<data/evidence>", "<business implication>"] }],', '    "chart": { "type": "bar", "title": "<descriptive chart title>", "labels": ["<Real Label 1>","<Real Label 2>","<Real Label 3>","<Real Label 4>"], "datasets": [{ "label": "<series>", "data": [100,250,380,520], "color": "#1E3A64" }] }', '  }', ']}', '', 'SLIDE TYPE RULES:', '- type=title: first slide only. Fields: title, subtitle. No bullets, no chart.', '- type=section_header: one per [SECTION: X] marker. Fields: title, subtitle. No bullets, no chart.', '- type=content: all other slides. MUST have exactly 4 bullets. Chart only on slides marked (include X chart).', '', 'CHART RULES:', '- Labels MUST be real industry-specific terms from the data.', '- NEVER use placeholder labels like L1, L2, L3, Item1, Category1.', '- bar: 4-6 labels, navy #1E3A64.', '- horizontalBar: 4-6 items ranked by value descending.', '- line: 6-8 time-series labels, navy #1E3A64 main.', '- doughnut: 4-6 segments summing to 100%.', '- Data values must be realistic for the industry.'].join('
');
const rules = ['MANDATORY CONTENT RULES:', '1. HEADLINES: Action statements with specific numbers.', '2. BULLETS: Exactly 4 bullets per content slide. Each 15-25 words with a quantifier.', '3. SUB_POINTS: Exactly 2 per bullet. First = evidence. Second = business implication.', '4. FINANCIALS: Include NPV, EBITDA impact, payback period where relevant.', '5. LANGUAGE: levers, EBITDA uplift, run-rate savings, value at stake, quick wins.', '6. FRAMEWORK: ' + (frameworkNote[deck_type] || ''), '7. INDUSTRY SPECIFICITY: Use ' + industry + '-specific terminology and named competitors.', '8. SECTION HEADERS: One section_header slide per [SECTION: X] marker.'].join('
');
let prompt = ['You are a Senior Partner at McKinsey & Company with 20 years of experience in ' + industry + ' sector engagements.', 'Your task: Build a world-class board-ready ' + (dtLabel[deck_type] || deck_type) + ' consulting deck for ' + client_name + '.', 'This deck will be presented to the C-suite and Board of Directors. Every slide must deliver a crisp data-backed insight with no filler.', '', data, '', slideStructure, '', jsonFmt, '', rules].join('
');
if (revision_notes) { prompt += '

REVISION FEEDBACK — incorporate ALL of the following into this revised deck:
' + revision_notes; }
return { json: { agent_input: prompt, engagement_id, deck_title, deck_type, requirements, client_name } };

const raw = $input.item.json.output;
